[normal]Powers of employment tribunals to make recommendations
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal](a)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]make a declaration as to the rights of the parties in relation to the matters to which the proceedings relate;
[normal](b)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]order the respondent to pay compensation to the complainant;
[normal](c)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]make
[normal] an appropriate recommendation.
[normal]Section 124(3) states:
[normal]“An appropriate recommendation is a recommendation that within a specified period the respondent takes specified steps for the purpose of obviating, or reducing the adverse effect of any matter to which the proceedings relate –
[normal](a)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]on the complainant;
[normal](b)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]on
[normal] any other person.”
